data_answer: Porcupines have long sharp teeth that never stop growing. It's easy to gnaw on wood with their strong sharp teeth. A tough orange coating protects their outer surface of their teeth. In the winter there is no grass or plants (that would usually be there in warmer seasons) to eat so they eat the tender woody parts of shrubs and trees. label: TRAINING
data_answer: Call World of Difference. Prickly porcupines wear quill-filled coats. No wonder they're called pricklepigs,quillpigs, and quillers. Even the word porcupine comes from french words that mean "spiny pig." But porcupines are not pigs. Like mice, squirrels, and beavers, they're rodents____animals with four front teeth built especially for gnawing. Call World Full of Food. It's easy to gnaw wood, with porcupine teeth. The front pairs___top and bottom___are strong and sharp. A tough orange coating protects their outer surface. As the porcupine gnaws, it sharpens these teeth by wearing away the backs faster then the front. Because the teeth grow for its whole life, they don't ever wear out. During winter, porcupines use their big front teeth to scrape off bark. Then they eat the tender woody parts of shrubs and trees. They also nibble salty soil. Call World of Words. Porcupines don't have much to say. That's because they spend a lot of their time alone. They "talk" a bit when they're looking for mates and caring for their young. Sometimes they warn enemies___such as fishers, mountain lions, wolves, and people___to leave them alone. Porcupine warnings come in three forms___sight, sound, nd smell. The sharp difference between the light and dark hair on an adult's back and tail makes it easy to spot at night. If an enemy appears, the porcupine turns its back and uses its body like a flag. "Go away," it's saying.

data_answer: The porkipines are very spiky they could be dangerous too. Porkipines are the most prickly animals in the world.They puff up when a predetor is near or close to it.Porkipines wear quill -filled coats.Porkipines are the largest rodents on the continent.Massesof the longest hair make them look bigger and heavier than they really are.The longest hair in the coat are called porkipines coat.They are soft ,fluffy hair forms a thick layer of fur all over the animal even on its underside.Its easy gnaw wood , with a porkipine teeth.The front pairs top and bottom are strong and sharp.A tough orange coating protects their outer surface.As the porkipine gnaws, it sharpens these teeth by wearing away the backs faster than the fronts.Becuase the teeth grow for its whole life, they don't even wear out.During winter, porkipines use their big front teeth to scrape off bark.Then they eat the tender woody parts of shrubs and trees.They also nibble needles on evergreens.In warmer months, porkipines snip off twigs and eat new buds and leaves.They munch on fruit,especiallyapples,but they usually toss away the cores.Alot of their summer food, including grass, clover, and dandilions, grows on the ground, but some grows in water.
